SYNOPSIS
========
   closure lambda(mixedÂ *arr, mixed)

DESCRIPTION
===========
   Constructs a lambda closure, like lambda function in LISP. The closure is 
   bound to the creating object, and thus can contain references to global 
   variables.

   The first argument is an array describing the arguments (symbols) passed to
   the closure upon evaluation by funcall(E) or apply(E).

HISTORY
=======
   - introduced (3.2@70)

SEE ALSO
========
   closure, unbound_lambda(E), apply(E), funcall(E), bind_lambda(E)
